            <p class="lead-strong">
              A product can look acceptable in reporting and still be economically weaker than it seems.
            </p>
            <p>
              In this case, the issue was not revenue visibility. It was decision quality. Standard margin told part of the story, but it ignored the operational burden attached to certain products and variants.
            </p>
            <p>
              That is where management can make the wrong call: protecting products that appear healthy while they quietly absorb scarce setup time, fragmented production effort, awkward fulfillment work, support attention, and valuable capacity.
