      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="reveal">The cost-to-serve logic behind the case</h2>
        <p class="section-intro reveal" style="--delay: 60ms;">
          The question of business this page responds to is: what sits between reported margin and real economic contribution, and why does it matter for decision-making?
        </p>

        <div class="split">
          <div class="panel panel-strong reveal-left" style="--delay: 120ms;">
            <h3>How the case reframes profitability</h3>
            <p>
              I structured the case around a product-level cost-to-serve lens that does not pretend every item carries the same operational burden. That creates a more realistic economic view than margin alone.
            </p>
            <p>
              The goal was not to force accounting precision where it does not belong. The goal was to make hidden operating burden visible enough for management to prioritize better.
